Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.60,0:00:03.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(400,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.32,0:00:24.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sometime ago, for the sake of living, we left behind our happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.33,0:00:31.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We deceived ourselves, clinging to this mere illusion as we danced...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.59,0:00:37.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With closed eyes, at the end of the horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.93,0:00:43.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was searching for your smiling face...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.35,0:00:51.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We embrace our dreams and continue on...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.36,0:00:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}within the swaying traces of memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.20,0:01:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Someday, I will once again grasp hold of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.29,0:01:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}these feelings I have locked away in my heart... Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.02,0:01:35.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Inherit the Fated Duel"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.58,0:01:46.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The two gods\N have the same Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.33,0:01:47.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.84,0:01:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Osiris...! Obelisk...!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.84,0:01:56.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}God against God...!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.51,0:01:58.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A battle of wits...!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.76,0:02:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Will they both perish?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.18,0:02:05.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This light...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.43,0:02:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are Osiris's and Obelisk's powers\N reacting to each other...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.16,0:02:22.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unreal...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.99,0:02:25.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me the\N entire tower blew up...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.75,0:02:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.84,0:02:39.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What in the...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.80,0:02:41.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Millennium Rod is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.97,0:02:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...glowing once again!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.53,0:03:05.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Millennium Puzzle...!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.81,0:03:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Wh-What...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.69,0:03:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...is going on here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.53,0:03:47.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's Ancient...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.91,0:03:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...Egypt!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.37,0:03:52.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.03,0:04:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's our two gods...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.95,0:04:26.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Everything's been destroyed...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.45,0:04:32.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}How... could this have happened...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.97,0:04:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This fog's engulfed the town...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.39,0:04:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What's this feeling...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.20,0:05:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This throbbing...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.12,0:05:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's coming from the royal palace...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.51,0:05:39.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like the High Priest of Darkness has\N conquered Heaven and Earth\N with his evil power...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.77,0:05:43.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even your divine right, the Millennium Items,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.69,0:05:46.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,were worthless against\N the Power of Darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.61,0:05:51.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In due time, this land will meet\N a terrible fate of destruction!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.62,0:05:57.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's the Millennium Puzzle!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.12,0:06:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why have you\N submitted to their will?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.46,0:06:03.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't misunderstand me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.96,0:06:07.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not as if I'm being {\i1}controlled{\i0} by them or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.09,0:06:09.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, I have no intentions of\N aiding {\i1}you{\i0} either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.43,0:06:15.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The will of my Millennium Rod and\N the power of my faithful servant\N shall {\i1}forever{\i0} be your enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.27,0:06:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Millennium Rod!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.69,0:06:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you've come here\N to settle the score?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.69,0:06:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is all the doing of destiny.\N I'm sure you have realized by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.86,0:06:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will defeat you\N with my own two hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.53,0:06:30.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my one and only wish!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.86,0:06:32.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You miscreant...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.70,0:06:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Wield the power of my servant,\N whose roar shakes the Heavens!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.50,0:06:38.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bear witness!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.71,0:06:42.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am going to wipe your servant\N from the face of this world!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.71,0:06:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Diaha!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.43,0:06:51.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arise! White Beast!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.01,0:06:55.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's the Blue-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.14,0:07:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I beckon the Black Magician sleeping\N within the stones of Wedju!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.27,0:07:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Black Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.57,0:07:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.16,0:07:15.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is it part of my lost memories?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.58,0:07:17.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.08,0:07:21.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But the Monster that\N came out of that stone tablet is\N without a doubt the Blue-Eyes...!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.26,0:07:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I see now!\N It's the same image as the two Duelists\N carved in the 3,000 year old slab!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.15,0:07:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What...?!\N What in the hell is happening?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.87,0:08:00.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The light's... starting to fade...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.91,0:08:02.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.77,0:08:23.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.56,0:08:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The gods are gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.61,0:08:38.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The gods disappeared...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.16,0:08:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Millennium Rod somehow\N awakened their memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.58,0:08:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But what the hell did they {\b0}see{\b1}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.01,0:08:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That scene that\N flashed through my mind...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.18,0:08:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What {\b0}was{\b1} it...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.05,0:08:59.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's absurd...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.02,0:09:03.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The fight between the Pharaoh the Priest...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.39,0:09:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He really existed...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.10,0:09:08.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The enemy I was fighting...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.36,0:09:10.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was {\b0}him{\b1}...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.44,0:09:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yugi!!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.53,0:09:20.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Pharaoh wielding\N the Black Magician...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.08,0:09:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...and the Priest wielding\N the White Beast...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.83,0:09:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They're exactly the same as us!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.04,0:09:34.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Part of that fight from 3,000 years ago\N was recorded on that palette...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.97,0:09:43.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That was a piece\N of my lost memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.06,0:09:48.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My lost memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.81,0:09:50.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm sure of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.65,0:09:54.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaiba, you're a part of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.82,0:09:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi! Don't tell me you saw\N the same vision I did!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.03,0:10:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba, I finally understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.74,0:10:09.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This battle is a fated Duel we've been\N fighting for the past 3,000 years!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.67,0:10:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Duel of destiny that\N has surpassed time itself!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.36,0:10:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Battle City...\N is a test to become a True Duelist,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.65,0:10:39.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as well as a battle\N to regain my memory!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.29,0:10:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the gods gone,\N this Duel's back to square one!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.09,0:10:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My Millennium Rod...\N And Yugi's Millennium Puzzle...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.67,0:11:00.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are their memories \Nsealed within them...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.13,0:11:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If that's the case,\N what the hell did they see?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.93,0:11:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain now, Kaiba!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.56,0:11:13.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My battle with you will open the\N first door to my memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.23,0:11:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could care less about some bizarre trick\N caused by the two gods colliding.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.90,0:11:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But whether that was reality or a mere illusion, it doesn't faze me in the slightest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.99,0:11:26.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will defeat you here and now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.29,0:11:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the only future I have is \Nto obtain the title "Duel King"!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.25,0:11:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We no longer {\i1}need{\i0}\N the gods in this fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.75,0:11:36.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.38,0:11:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,, Even though my god is gone, I haven't\N declared the end of my turn yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.68,0:11:46.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set a reverse card and end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.35,0:11:50.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In the end, the only thing\N that can defeat you is my servant\N that surpasses even God...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.60,0:11:52.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Blue-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.35,0:11:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.06,0:11:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This isn't it...!\N This isn't the card I need...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.78,0:12:01.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's one key card\N I still haven't drawn yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.40,0:12:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaiba has but one\N reverse card on the field...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.78,0:12:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But he still needs to be\N wary of an attack...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.50,0:12:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What are you gonna do now,\N Your Highness?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.21,0:12:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to Summon\N Illusion Beast Gazelle on this turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.39,0:12:27.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now I activate my reverse Trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.81,0:12:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Clone Reproduction!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.44,0:12:34.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Clone?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.48,0:12:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Trap clones the Monster you have on the field and places its copy on my field!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.78,0:12:43.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, Yugi, what's your next move?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.53,0:12:47.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll place another card face-down!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.49,0:12:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.91,0:12:53.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's {\i1}wrong{\i0} with you, Yugi?\N Aren't you being a little too {\i1}cautious{\u0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.17,0:13:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that prudence of yours will only\N lead you to a future of destruction!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.26,0:13:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next turn, I'm going to\N sacrifice the clone of your Monster\N to Summon a {\i1}new{\i0} servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.68,0:13:12.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now that the gods are in the Graveyard,\N the next Monster Kaiba will Summon...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.27,0:13:15.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't! Not the Blue-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.11,0:13:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But it costs two sacrifices to\N Summon an Eight-Star Monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.53,0:13:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if he has it in his hand, he won't be able to Summon it next turn...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.45,0:13:31.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Will I be able to draw my key card\N before he does...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.45,0:13:32.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.49,0:13:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.33,0:13:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi... Let me tell you something...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.29,0:13:41.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Blue-Eyes is already\N resting in my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.71,0:13:48.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may think I'm not able\N to Summon it this turn...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.18,0:13:52.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but this card will change\N all perception you had of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.10,0:13:55.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Magic Card\N Cost Down from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.69,0:14:03.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cost Down is a Magic Card that\N lowers the Level of a Monster Card\N by two stars for one turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.65,0:14:04.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.99,0:14:07.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}His Eight-Star Blue-Eyes\N will become a Six-Star...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.53,0:14:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He'll be able to Summon it\N with just one sacrifice!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.66,0:14:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a good look, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.53,0:14:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is {\i1}not{\i0} an illusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.16,0:14:15.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the form of the ultimate Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.25,0:14:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I offer the Clone Monster as a tribute!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.58,0:14:23.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth, Blue-Eyes White Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.42,0:14:29.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My brother's Blue-Eyes is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.72,0:14:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For him to Summon\N the Blue-Eyes like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.60,0:14:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Heh! I can see the end of this match!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.69,0:14:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi! The ancient illusions are over!\NThis is the real world and\N your defeat along with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.65,0:14:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue-Eyes! Attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.86,0:14:50.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Burst Stream of Destruction!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.70,0:14:54.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gazelle is destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.37,0:14:58.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn ends there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.71,0:15:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So bring it, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.87,0:15:05.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But all your Monsters with\N less than 3000 Attack Points\N will go down in flames!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.17,0:15:10.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.89,0:15:20.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If that vision was true...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.35,0:15:24.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...then the next card I draw\N has already decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.65,0:15:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It all depends on this draw...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.91,0:15:38.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Will I be able to flip to the next\N page of my lost memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.58,0:15:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.25,0:15:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba, you saw it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.54,0:15:50.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The carving of a Duelist's battle\N made 3,000 years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.22,0:15:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether they were\N a Pharaoh or a Priest...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.64,0:15:55.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter {\i1}who{\i0} they were!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.93,0:16:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was carved there was\N their spirit as Duelists!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.35,0:16:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that spirit \Nhas been passed onto us!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.48,0:16:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to prove to you that\N this wasn't an illusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.15,0:16:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Magic Card \NResurrection of the Dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.74,0:16:13.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Awaken!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.49,0:16:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The soul of the magician\N sleeping in the Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.20,0:16:19.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Magician...?\N He couldn't have...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.95,0:16:21.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come out, Black Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.79,0:16:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Damn you, Yugi...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.34,0:16:32.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When Life Shaver forced him\N to discard a card, he sent\N Black Magician to the Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.26,0:16:34.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And this scene...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.48,0:16:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From before...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.52,0:16:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A battle from my memories was recorded\N on that ancient palette!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.36,0:16:55.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if this Duel is a piece of\N the puzzle of memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.82,0:16:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.91,0:16:59.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must defeat you!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.74,0:17:02.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to get back\N my lost memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.33,0:17:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But neither the stone slab or the\N vision shown to us revealed what\N happens beyond this point...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.79,0:17:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What was the result of the battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.92,0:17:15.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But even if everything in this Duel has\N been destined from the beginning...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.80,0:17:19.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Supposing that elaborate vision\N we saw {\b0}was{\b1} in fact reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.81,0:17:23.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I decide what happens on\N my road of battle myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.77,0:17:26.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.77,0:17:29.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set another reverse card!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.69,0:17:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Blue-Eyes has 3000 Attack Points...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.07,0:17:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And the Black Magician opposes\N it with 2500 Attack Points...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.37,0:17:44.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Black Magician can't beat it without any additional assistance in Attack Strength...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.83,0:17:48.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But now I have two\N reverse cards on the field...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.88,0:17:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And one of them is\N Spellbook of Black Magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.30,0:17:57.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Its effects will increase Black Magician's Attack Power by 500 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.18,0:18:00.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But that won't bring it higher\N than the Blue-Eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.72,0:18:03.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My only chance is to wait\N until he attacks me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.48,0:18:05.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.48,0:18:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph! The Black Magician?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.81,0:18:11.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you\N saw the same vision I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.69,0:18:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But let me tell you the {\i1}truth{\i0}\N about that ridiculous "vision" we saw!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.94,0:18:23.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was nothing more than subliminal images\N our brains stored when we saw the carving\N of the Priest and the Pharaoh!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.08,0:18:27.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Pharaoh from 3,000 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.25,0:18:30.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make me laugh, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.25,0:18:35.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As far as I'm concerned,\N you're nothing more than a naive bigot\N who's trapped in his own fantasies!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.26,0:18:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're just a prisoner bound\N by a chain of the past!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.22,0:18:39.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.51,0:18:42.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no light for those\N who are shackled to the past!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.47,0:18:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you turn your back on the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.22,0:18:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you tread down the road\N of nostalgia and defeat!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.14,0:18:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.56,0:18:52.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one reverse card!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.40,0:18:55.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I activate a\N Magic Card from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.53,0:18:58.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Life-Shaving Card Treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.32,0:19:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm able to draw until I hold five cards\N in my hand, provided I discard my\N entire hand five turns later!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.45,0:19:06.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Hand Reinforcement card!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.70,0:19:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The reverse cards on his field...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.29,0:19:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}One of them must be\N a Magic Card to increase the\N Black Magician's Attack Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.88,0:19:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And the other one...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.59,0:19:19.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A Trap Card activated\N by Blue-Eyes' attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.13,0:19:22.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hexagram Curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.51,0:19:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've analyzed all of your strategies\N through this Battle City Tournament\N and long before it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.06,0:19:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know exactly\N what you're going to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.40,0:19:38.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can see through your deck\N as if it were made of {\i1}glass{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.69,0:19:42.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this turn... I'm going\N to Summon {\i1}this{\i0} Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.49,0:19:43.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.82,0:19:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show yourself, Lord of Dragons!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.24,0:19:49.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Lord of Dragons...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.25,0:19:56.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As long as he has the Lord of Dragons\N on the field, his Blue-Eyes is safe\N from his opponent's Magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.30,0:19:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Next turn...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.46,0:20:01.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll crush you with one blow!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.63,0:20:05.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's read my strategy\N inside and out...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.14,0:20:06.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What should I do...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.76,0:20:08.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.10,0:20:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.93,0:20:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I've planned even\N {\b0}farther{\b1} than that, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.85,0:20:15.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll Summon Magnet Warrior Beta!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.86,0:20:16.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In Defense Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.74,0:20:24.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are you going to attack\N my Lord of Dragons with\N the Black Magician, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.41,0:20:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I attack Lord of Dragons\N with Black Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.83,0:20:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black Magic!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.62,0:20:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You fell for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.83,0:20:33.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap Card, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.83,0:20:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mechanical Magic Mirror!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.92,0:20:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mechanical Magic Mirror is a card\N that lets me activate a Magic Card\N from my opponent's Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.55,0:20:50.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using that effect,\N I'll activate this Magic Card\N lying dormant in your Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.39,0:20:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This{\i0} card!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.81,0:20:54.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Resurrection of the Dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.65,0:20:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the Monster I choose to revive...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.94,0:21:00.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is {\i1}him{\i0}!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.61,0:21:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Obelisk!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.66,0:21:08.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gods can only be raised for one turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.58,0:21:10.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he can't attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.04,0:21:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But despite that effect...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.41,0:21:16.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...he will act as my\N impenetrable shield, acting as\N the perfect defense for my servants!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.21,0:21:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.34,0:21:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, you can no longer stop\N your Black Magic attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.38,0:21:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.76,0:21:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The attack is bounced back,\N and is dealt to the player as damage!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.77,0:21:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We finally have a turn\N in Life Point scores!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.04,0:21:54.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaiba-kun and Yugi saw a glimpse of their past in the clash between Obelisk and Osiris.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.96,0:22:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But Kaiba-{\i0}kun{\i1} denies everything he saw and declares that he will send Yugi to Hell along with his past!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.42,0:22:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And Kaiba finally gets all three of his Blue-Eyes on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.97,0:22:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As he's pressed into a corner, Yugi sees an image of Jounouchi.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.93,0:22:10.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's right, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.10,0:22:12.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't forget your promise with Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.68,0:22:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.39,0:22:16.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"The Promise Between Friends: The Red-Eyes Black Dragon"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.44,0:22:17.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Duel standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.34,0:22:32.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The houses lined down the street drifting by being dyed red
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.68,0:22:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I notice pain, it'll turn into happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.27,0:22:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Every time people wipe away tears, they understand bonds
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.37,0:23:01.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The warm strength that you gave me will change into kindness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.79,0:23:10.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Overflowing feelings don't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.05,0:23:20.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll live while I feel it, for me to be myself
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.90,0:23:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Healed by overflowing friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.16,0:23:35.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our fated encounter is a truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.56,0:23:44.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and someday we'll be able to understand each other
